{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_2gmi6stist0o_1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\t<<<<<<< HEAD\n3\tevery: 1h\n4\ttickScript: .kody/scripts/auto-resolve-tick.sh\n5\t=======\n6\tdisabled: true\n7\tworker: kody\n8\t>>>>>>> origin/dev\n9\t---\n10\t\n11\t# auto resolve\n12\t\n13\t## Job\n14\t\n15\tFor every open, non-draft pull request that is not yet merged: if it has a merge conflict, post the comment `@kody resolve` on the PR. Otherwise do nothing.\n16\t\n17\tA PR enters this job's scope as soon as it becomes ready for review (non-draft, open). It leaves scope when it is merged or closed.\n18\t\n19\t## Allowed Commands\n20\t\n21\t`@kody resolve`\n22\t\n23\t## Restrictions\n24\t\n25\t- Only act when the PR's mergeable state is `CONFLICTING`. Skip `MERGEABLE`, `UNKNOWN`, draft, merged, closed.\n26\t- Do not modify the issue, the PR body, the PR title, labels (except as instructed below), or any code.\n27\t- Do not re-issue `@kody resolve` on the same head SHA more than 2 times.\n28\t- After 2 failed attempts on a SHA: post `kody resolve stuck — needs human` and add label `kody:stuck-conflict`; skip until SHA changes or label is removed.\n29\t\n30\t## Tick procedure — REQUIRED\n31\t\n32\tThis tick is **fully scripted**. The script [auto-resolve-tick.sh](.kody/scripts/auto-resolve-tick.sh) is the **single source of truth** for which PRs are candidates, what state mutations to make, and which comments to post.\n33\t\n34\tA previous iteration of this job used prose enumeration and **hallucinated** PRs #122 and #124 as conflicting (both are long-closed) — then posted a real `@kody resolve` comment on closed PR #122. Do not repeat that.\n35\t\n36\tYou **MUST**:\n37\t\n38\t1. Run exactly: `bash .kody/scripts/auto-resolve-tick.sh`\n39\t2. Emit the script's stdout verbatim — including the markdown summary table and the `kody-job-next-state` fenced block at the end.\n40\t\n41\tYou **MUST NOT**:\n42\t\n43\t- Call `gh pr list` yourself.\n44\t- Filter, decide actions, post comments, or mutate state outside the script.\n45\t- Use any prior knowledge of PR numbers in this repo. The script's output is your only data source for this tick.\n46\t- Re-run the script (it has side effects). One invocation per tick.\n47\t\n48\tIf the script exits non-zero, surface its stderr and emit a state block with the prior `perPr` unchanged so progress isn't lost.\n49\t\n50\t## State shape\n51\t\n52\t`data.perPr` is a map of PR number → `{ lastSha: string, attempts: number, stuck: boolean }`.\n53\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74943ded-d25e-4e2b-9641-eb289f2bf493","uuid":"c09f3196-60e7-48d1-b220-13e5002c0300","timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:49:43.157Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/A-Guy/A-Guy/.kody/jobs/auto-resolve.md","content":"---\n<<<<<<< HEAD\nevery: 1h\ntickScript: .kody/scripts/auto-resolve-tick.sh\n=======\ndisabled: true\nworker: kody\n>>>>>>> origin/dev\n---\n\n# auto resolve\n\n## Job\n\nFor every open, non-draft pull request that is not yet merged: if it has a merge conflict, post the comment `@kody resolve` on the PR. Otherwise do nothing.\n\nA PR enters this job's scope as soon as it becomes ready for review (non-draft, open). It leaves scope when it is merged or closed.\n\n## Allowed Commands\n\n`@kody resolve`\n\n## Restrictions\n\n- Only act when the PR's mergeable state is `CONFLICTING`. Skip `MERGEABLE`, `UNKNOWN`, draft, merged, closed.\n- Do not modify the issue, the PR body, the PR title, labels (except as instructed below), or any code.\n- Do not re-issue `@kody resolve` on the same head SHA more than 2 times.\n- After 2 failed attempts on a SHA: post `kody resolve stuck — needs human` and add label `kody:stuck-conflict`; skip until SHA changes or label is removed.\n\n## Tick procedure — REQUIRED\n\nThis tick is **fully scripted**. The script [auto-resolve-tick.sh](.kody/scripts/auto-resolve-tick.sh) is the **single source of truth*